ted to\ntopological representation theory of EDCL, transferring into the distributive\ncase important results from the topological representation theory of contact\nalgebras. It is shown that under minor additional assumptions on distributive\nlattices as extensionality of the definable relations of overlap or underlap\none can preserve the good topological interpretations of regions as regular\nclosed or regular open sets in topological space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jan 2019 18:37:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-30"}
