Williamson-Hall equation, the microstrain of the samples increased upon\nincreasing x and for Nd0.95Ca0.05FeAsO0.8F0.2 sample was grown approximately\nthree times in comparison to the pure sample. So, it is noticeable that there\nis a relation between the structural properties and superconductivity in our\nsamples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Jan 2019 14:56:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-31"}
